<text id="04-procedure" title="pytest Mocking — Procedure" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="medium">
  <summary>Step-by-step procedure for applying python-pytest-mocking.</summary>

    <section title="Step 1: Identify external boundary">
      <p>Input: Source</p>
      <p>Action: Locate I/O / external dep the test must avoid.</p>
      <p>Output: Boundary list.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2: Find use site">
      <p>Input: Boundary</p>
      <p>Action: Locate the importing module that calls the dep.</p>
      <p>Output: Patch target string.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3: Patch with autospec">
      <p>Input: mocker available</p>
      <p>Action: mocker.patch(target, autospec=True) or new=AsyncMock(...).</p>
      <p>Output: Mock active in test.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4: Assert calls">
      <p>Input: Mock active</p>
      <p>Action: mock.assert_called_once_with(expected_args).</p>
      <p>Output: Behaviour pinned.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5: Spy when needed">
      <p>Input: Real impl desired</p>
      <p>Action: mocker.spy(obj, 'method').</p>
      <p>Output: Observability without override.</p>
    </section>
</text>
